message.content:
The best modern approach is flexbox. Here's how:

```css
body {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  height: 100vh;
}
```

This centers the div both horizontally and vertically. `align-items` handles vertical centering, `justify-content` handles horizontal, and `height: 100vh` makes the container full viewport height.

Absolutely! Grid is just as good for centering:

```css
body {
  display: grid;
  place-items: center;
  height: 100vh;
}
```

`place-items: center;` is a shorthand that centers both horizontally and vertically. It combines `align-items` and `justify-items`. Grid and Flexbox are both great options - choose based on your layout needs.
